I reproduced this with the following small program:
```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"os"
	"strings"
)

func main() {
	k := "LIB"
	v := "$(PREFIX)"
	// config.go:271
	reset := func(s *[]string) {
		getenv := func(name string) string {
			for i := range *s {
				val := strings.SplitN((*s)[i], "=", 2)
				if len(val) == 2 && val[0] == name {
					return val[1]
				}
			}
			return name
		}
		n := []string{}
		for i := range *s {
			if !strings.HasPrefix((*s)[i], k+"=") {
				n = append(n, (*s)[i])
			}
			v = os.Expand(v, getenv)
		}
		n = append(n, k+"="+v)
		*s = n
	}
	// config.go:290

	m := []string{"PATH=/usr/bin"}
	reset(&m)
	fmt.Print(m)
}
```

```
$ go1.10.4 run test.go
[PATH=/usr/bin LIB=(PREFIX)]
$ go run test.go
[PATH=/usr/bin LIB=$(PREFIX)]
```

This is a behaviour change in [go1.11](https://github.com/golang/go/commit/7bf631e1fc55839a6bff404a91597326e1addc10#diff-b30ffd1cf7612ccebac97fced83d5106) described in https://github.com/golang/go/issues/24345. 

My suggestion on how to address this:
- Specify that version 1.11 or higher is required here: https://github.com/containers/buildah/blob/master/install.md#installation-from-github
- Add a test to ensure correct behaviour

Does that sound fine? If so, I'll put in a PR.
